main event: Unidentified object sighting by the crew of the USS Durante
interesting points: The object was described as round, pin-head white in color.
The object was tracked visually for 9 minutes, with its position obtained using celestial navigation.
The object was moving in a straight path, approximately 270 degrees true, and was lost in the haze on the horizon.
The report includes details on the location, time, and weather conditions of the sighting.
The sighting was made by several highly reliable witnesses, including the navigator, officer of the deck, and assistant navigator.
witnesses: LCDR USN, LTJG USNR OOD, CMI LSN ASST NAV
